<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 1 Killed, 1 Injured in Railway Accident in Egypt </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, September 27 (Xinhua) -- One person died and another
injured Sunday in a traffic accident occurring on the railway
linking Cairo and Alexandria.
</P>
<P>
A passenger train rammed into a truck, whose driver ignoreed
signals and crashed his way into a crossing, early in the day,
killing the assistant driver of the train and injuring the truck
driver, police sources said.
</P>
<P>
No casualties were inflicted on the passengers on the train,
the sources added, without detailing the condition of the truck
driver.
</P>
<P>
One of the train wagons was immediately derailed and fire broke
out in an electric transformer. The signal system was severely
damaged and traffic on the Cairo-Alexandria line was temporarily
interrupted.
</P>
<P>
Cranes were rushed to the scene to clear the area. So far the
two-way traffic has yet to be restored. 
</P>
</TEXT>
