<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hakkinen Wins Luxembourg Grand Prix </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, September 27 (Xinhua) -- Finland's Mika Hakkinen won the
Luxembourg Formula One Grand Prix in Nuerburgring, Germany, on
Sunday, beating Germany's Michael Schumacher to second place.
</P>
<P>
Hakkinen, who came into the race with his overall score tied
with Schumacher at 80 points, now gained a four-point advantage
with 90 points against Schumacher's 86.
</P>
<P>
This year's champion will be decided by the outcome of final
race in Japan, where Hakkinen can afford to finish second and
still clinch his first championship title.
</P>
<P>
He finished the race distance of 305.252 kilometers in one
hour, 23.718 seconds, beating Schumacher by 2.2 seconds.
</P>
<P>
David Coulthard of Britain was third, while his compatriot
Eddie Irvine finished fourth.
</P>
<P>
Heinz-Harald Frentzen of Germany was fifth, while Italy's
Giancarlo Fisichella finished sixth.
</P>
<P>
On the overall standings, Coutlthard was third at 52 points,
Irvine fourth at 41 while Jacques Villeneuve of Canada fifth at
20. 
</P>
</TEXT>
