<HEADLINE> Kohl Defeated by SPD Candidate Schroeder, TV Projections </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, September 27 (Xinhua) -- German opposition Social
Democratic Party (SPD) candidate Gerhard Schroeder won the general
elections Sunday, ending the 16-year era of Chancellor Helmut
Kohl, according to the first exit polls on ZDF and ARD TV networks.
</P>
<P>
The SPD took 41 percent of the vote for the lower house of
parliament, or Bundestag, the ZDF projection said.
</P>
<P>
Kohl's Christian Democratic Union (CDU)/Christian Social Union
(CSU) parties took 35 percent of the vote.
</P>
<P>
The ARD network gave the SPD 41.2 percent of the vote against
35.7 percent for Kohl's Christian Democrats. 
</P>
