<HEADLINE> (Urgent) Kohl Concedes Defeat </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, September 27 (Xinhua) -- The incumbent German chancellor
Helmut Kohl has conceded defeat after his conservative alliance
was beaten by the main opposition Social Democratic Party (SPD)
and his chancellor candidate, Gerhard Schroeder, at the general
elections Sunday.
</P>
<P>
"It is clear that I should take the responsibility for this
election defeat, without if and but," said Kohl in Bonn after the
revelations of the preliminary projections which put the SPD some
five percentage points ahead of his conservative alliance.
</P>
<P>
Kohl also declared that he would not be available for
reelection as the chairman of his Christian Democratic Union (CDU)
party.
</P>
<P>
Kohl also congratulated his challenger Schroeder on his
victory. "It is a personal success for Gerhard Schroeder," he
said. 
</P>
