<HEADLINE> Autopsy Report: Matei Dies Due to Breathing in Own Vomit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, September 27 (Xinhua) -- Sorin Matei, the escaped
Romanian criminal who held four hostages in central Athens
Wednesday, died after breathing in his own vomit, showed an
initial autopsy report Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Four coroners assigned to conduct an autopsy on Matei, who died
suddenly Saturday in the Korydallos prison hospital, said that
Matei had choked to death while he was heavily sedated and bound
and that he should never have been moved to the prison.
</P>
<P>
The 27-Romanian convict had been under sedation and heavy guard
since late Wednesday after holding police at bay for some six
hours and threatening to detonate a hand grenade, which exploded
and injured 12 people, including 10 police officers.
</P>
<P>
Matei's lawyer said after the announcement of the coroners'
findings that there were still many questions about Matei's death
that demanded answers.
</P>
<P>
A report on the definitive cause of Matei's death will be
issued on completion of all toxicology and other tests. 
</P>
</TEXT>
