<HEADLINE> Iran Condemns U.S. Delivery of Jet-fighters to </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, September 27 (Xinhua) -- Iran on Sunday condemned
the U.S. decision to provide Israel with more jet-fighters and
sophisticated arms, saying that the move indicated Washington's
double-standard policies.
</P>
<P>
Such "irresponsible" support of the U.S. for Israel's military
build-up ran counter to all global efforts to protect
international peace and security, Iranian Foreign Ministry
spokesman Mahmoud Mohammadi said.
</P>
<P>
He said that Israel, backed by the U.S. and certain
western countries, has turned the occupied lands into a depot
of modern arms posing serious threat to the stability and
security of the region and the world, the official news agency
IRNA reported.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman noted that Washington continues providing Israel
with sophisticated weapons and supports the entity's nuclear
activities and terrorist acts on the one hand, and speaks of
the Middle East peace talks on the other.
</P>
<P>
He said that the U.S. knows well that such support would
bear no fruit but it would rather further endanger regional
peace and stability, encourage Israel to continue with its
aggressive and expansionist policies in Palestine and the region.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. move is an attempt to divert public opinion from
the dangerous facts in the region, he added. 
</P>
