<HEADLINE> Tanzania to Export 500 Tons of Cashew Nuts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, September 27 (Xinhua) -- The Netherlands has
ordered 500 tons of cashew nuts from east Tanzania's Coast Region
this farming season.
</P>
<P>
The Regional Commissioner, Nicodemus Banduka, said in Kibaha
of the region recently that the crop could earn local farmers
some 200 million Shillings (about 300,000 U.S. Dollars),
according to reports reaching here Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Banduka said the region has launched a special drive to boost
the production of the main cash crop through enactment of laws.
Meanwhile, farmers in the region have established 65 cashew nut
processing centers to increment the value of the crop.
</P>
<P>
The region, he said, is serious about reviving the production
of the crop whose production has been dwindling these years due
to lack of proper care.
</P>
<P>
Last farming season, the region produced 8,000 tons of cashew
nuts, compared with 34,252 tons in the 1993/94 fiscal year, he
said.
</P>
<P>
Cashew nut is a major foreign exchange earner of Tanzania.
Statistics show that cashew nut output in the east African
country hit 90,000 tons last season. 
</P>
</TEXT>
