<HEADLINE> Schroeder Pledges Continuity in German Foreign Policy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, September 27 (Xinhua) -- Gerhard Schroeder, the winner of
Germany's national election Sunday, declared that he would
maintain continuity in Germany's foreign policy pursued by the
government of the outgoing chancellor Helmut Kohl.
</P>
<P>
In a first policy declaration issued after an apparent clear
victory over Kohl's conservative alliance as indicated by
preliminary television projections, Schroeder said he has three
major priorities: "economic stability, inner security and above
all also continuity in foreign policy."
</P>
<P>
He also stressed that his most important goal is the combat
against mass unemployment in the country.
</P>
<P>
Schroeder also thanked the voters for their support and
described his success in the general elections as a clear
confirmation of his concept of the so-called political "New
Center," under which he pledges to combine modernity with social
justice in Germany. 
</P>
