<HEADLINE> Blair Congratulates Schroeder on Election Victory </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 27 (Xinhua) -- British Prime Minister Tony
Blair Sunday congratulated Gerhard Schroeder upon his election as
Germany's next chancellor, saying results of the German election
were a "tremendous thing."
</P>
<P>
A Downing Street spokesman told reporters that Blair had a
telephone conversation with Schroeder early Sunday, praising his
election campaign as a "great victory."
</P>
<P>
Blair told Schroeder in the 10-minute conversation that the
election results were also a "personal triumph" for Schroeder and
he was looking forward to an early meeting.
</P>
<P>
"It is a tremendous result for Gerhard Schroeder, and a great
personal triumph for him. It's a tremendous thing that we will now
see center-left government in Britain, France, and Germany," Blair
said.
</P>
<P>
Blair described Schroeder as a man of tremendous ability and
expressed his conviction that he was sure they would all work
closely together to create a prosperous Europe.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Blair paid tribute to outgoing German Chancellor
Helmut Kohl by saying, "I pay tribute to Helmut Kohl for all of
the things he has done for Europe."
</P>
<P>
Preliminary projections conducted by German television networks
showed that Schroeder's Social Democratic Party has won 41.2
percent of the vote against 35.7 percent for Kohl's Christian
Democratic Union. 
</P>
