<HEADLINE> Iran to Issue Green Cards for Refugees </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, September 27 (Xinhua) -- An senior Iranian official
announced on Sunday that Iran would issue green cards for
refugees living in Iran.
</P>
<P>
Farhad Barikani, an official from the Interior Ministry in
charge of the refugees camps said in Dezful, southwestern
province of Khuzestan that all foreign subjects such as Afghan
and Iraqi refugees would soon have their green cards.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to the official news agency IRNA, Barikani said
that green cards would be issued for all foreign subjects in
the current Iranian year (started March 21) to allow them to
go anywhere throughout the country, after they are identified.
</P>
<P>
He said that some 2 million foreign citizens are living in
Iran, of which nearly 1.4 million are Afghans.
</P>
<P>
Iran continues its humanitarian assistance to Iraqi and
Afghan refugees and the government will never force refugees to
leave the country unless they want to return their indigenous
countries, the official added. 
</P>
