</P>
<P>
TEHRAN -- Folk dances and symphony are back on the stage in
Iran after nearly two decades, as the government vows to promote
the status of tourism in the country.
</P>
<P>
Dressed in local colorful costumes, of course in light of
Islamic dressing codes, six Iranian actresses on Sunday performed
a ground-breaking folk dance for senior Iranian officials and
foreign diplomats.
</P>
<P>
The 1979 Islamic Revolution has influenced every aspect of life
of the Iranian people, and performances of folk dances and western
symphony have been rare since. (BC-Iran-Tourism) 
