<HEADLINE> Air Hostess Arrested in Nepal for Possessing Currencies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, September 28 (Xinhua) -- A senior air hostess of the
state-owned Royal Nepal Airlines Corporation was arrested here
Sunday for possessing various foreign currencies and traveler
cheques of various denominations, the Nepali official RSS news
agency reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
Police at the Tribhuvan International Airport recovered from
Shanta Khanal's hand bag and baggage 1.3995 million Indian rupees,
109,715 U.S. dollars and 660,000 Japanese yen, RSS said.
</P>
<P>
Other currencies seized were those of Saudi Arabia, Qatar,
Italy, Germany, Singapore, Australia, Britain, France,
Switzerland, Brunei, Canada and Hong Kong, which ranged from 700
to 100,000 in value.
</P>
<P>
Police also seized traveler cheques valued at 15,460 U.S.
dollars and 101,000 Japanese yen, and cheques amounting to
24870.55 U.S. dollars issued in the name of different persons, RSS
said.
</P>
<P>
It said the air hostess was about to board the RA 407
Kathmandu-Bangkok-Singapore flight.
</P>
<P>
Investigation was under way, the news agency added.
</P>
<P>
The Tribhuvan International Airport, the only one of its kind
in Nepal, has been in the spotlight for currency and gold
smuggling. 
</P>
