<HEADLINE> Singapore's Manufacturing Output Drops in August </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, September 28 (Xinhua) -- Singapore's manufacturing
output in August 1998 fell by 6.6 percent compared with a year
ago, keeping a downturn in all major clusters -- electronics,
engineering and chemical, the country's Economic Development Board
(EDB) said Monday.
</P>
<P>
But the total cumulative output for the first eight months of
1998 grew by 0.4 percent compared with the same period of 1997, it
said in a press release.
</P>
<P>
According to the EDB, monthly output of the electronics and
engineering clusters declined 9 and 4.7 percent respectively while
the output of the chemical cluster was 0.3 percent lower than that
of August 1997 despite a 26.5 percent increase in the monthly
output of pharmaceuticals.
</P>
<P>
In the accumulative output for the first eight months of this
year, the electronics cluster registered a 3.4 percent decline
than a year ago while chemicals and engineering clusters enjoyed
12.9 and 3.6 percent increases respectively, the EDB said.
</P>
</TEXT>
