are advancing towards other areas still under the control of the
Khalili militia," the radio said.
</P>
<P>
The Punjab district includes strategic supply routes for the
Hezb-e-Wahdat, which has suffered heavy losses in Bamyan province
since the capital, Bamyan City, fell to the Taliban forces on
September 13.
</P>
<P>
Khalili's group is one of the main factions in the anti-Taliban
Northern Alliance, along with those of Afghan ex-defense minister
Ahmad Masood and ethnic-Uzbek warlord Rashid Dostum. 
