<HEADLINE> Philippines' Rice Stock Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, September 28 (Xinhua) -- The Philippines' total rice
stock as of September 1 stood at 1.66 million metric tons, up by
26.2 percent from last year's 1.31 million metric tons, the
Department of Agriculture reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
Data released by the Bureau of Agricultural Statistics show
that the stock was good for 79 days' supply for the country's
nearly 70 million population.
</P>
<P>
Compared with the previous month's level, the September 1 stock
was 5 percent lower with a major drawdown of 15.3 percent in stock
positions of households.
</P>
<P>
About 55 percent of the stock was with the National Food
Authority, 25 percent kept by the households and 20 percent held
in commercial warehouses.
</P>
<P>
The bureau said the total corn stock as of September 1, on the
other hand, reached 363,600 metric tons, or 29 percent higher than
1997.
</P>
<P>
Compared with the previous month's level, the current corn
stock position posted a 133.7 percent increment with hefty
increases recorded in the stock positions of the households and
the National Food Authority. 
</P>
</TEXT>
