<HEADLINE> HK Manufacturers Celebrate China's National Day </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September (Xinhua) -- The Chinese Manufacturer's
Association (CMA) of Hong Kong held a reception here Monday to
celebrate the 49th anniversary of the founding of the People's
Republic of China.
</P>
<P>
Michael Suen, acting administrative secretary of the Hong Kong
Special Administrative Region (SAR), and other SAR government
officials attended the reception.
</P>
<P>
Among others present at the reception were officials of
institutions of the Central Government in Hong Kong, foreign
consuls in Hong Kong, members of the Legislative Council of the
SAR, Hong Kong deputies of the National People's Congress and Hong
Kong members of the National Committee of the Chinese People's
Political Consultative Conference and leading local businessmen.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the gathering, CMA President Herbert Liang said that
China had laid a new milestone in the course of economic reform
this year by formulating and implementing various economic
policies.
</P>
<P>
In addition, positive and pragmatic attitude continued to be
adopted and clear objectives for the economic reform had been
established to equip the country for future challenges.
</P>
<P>
Liang said he strongly believed that with those far-reaching
and conductive objectives as well as policies, a strong foundation
for China could be built up and the economy of China would then
continue to prosper in the next century.
</P>
<P>
Liang said that Hong Kong's role as the important gateway for
China's mainland to international markets had to be better
capitalized to enhance the economic cooperation between Hong Kong,
the mainland and foreign countries.
</P>
<P>
Economic cooperation between Hong Kong and the mainland is
already growing closer and closer and the new developments of the
mainland would be effective in keeping the stability and
prosperity of Hong Kong, Liang noted.
</P>
<P>
The CMA was established in 1934. With over 3,700 member
companies from various sectors of industry and trade, it is one of
the oldest and most representative industrial associations in Hong
Kong.  
