<HEADLINE> China Says Congratulations to Germany's New Leader </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 28 (Xinhua) -- China conveyed its
congratulations to the German Social Democratic Party on winning
the national election, Foreign Ministry spokesman Tang Guoqiang
said today.
</P>
<P>
In response to a reporter's question, Tang said that the Sunday
election, as Germany's last national election in this
century, has attracted public attention.
</P>
<P>
"We congratulate the German Social Democratic Party on winning
the national election. China has always valued its relations with
Germany," Tang noted, adding that maintaining and developing long
and stable relations of friendly cooperation is a major part of
China's foreign policy, and conforms to the fundamental interests
of the peoples of the two nations.
</P>
<P>
He said China believes that with Gerhard Schroeder taking the
post of Chancellor, the existing Sino-German friendly relationship
will continue to grow.
</P>
<P>
Tang also said that during the tenure of Chancellor Helmut Kohl,
the two countries witnessed an overall development of
bilateral relations, and that the Chinese government and people
will never forget Chancellor Kohl's efforts in promoting these
relations. 
</P>
