<HEADLINE> CPPCC Vice-Chairman Meets Taiwan Entrepreneurs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 28 (Xinhua) -- Wan Guoquan, vice-chairman of
the National Committee of the Chinese People's Political
Consultative Conference (CPPCC), said here today that developing
cross-straits relations and realizing direct postal, commercial
and transport links are in the common interests of compatriots on
both sides of the Taiwan Straits.
</P>
<P>
In a meeting with presidents of the associations of
Taiwan-funded enterprises in the mainland, Wan said the central
government has always advocated developing cross-straits economic
cooperation on the basis of equality and mutual benefits.
</P>
<P>
He also quoted President Jiang Zemin as saying that "we are not
in favor of obstructing cross-straits economic cooperation by the
effect of political disparity."
</P>
<P>
The mainland is now politically stable, with a developing
economy that has huge market potential for investment, Wan said,
voicing the hope that more Taiwan compatriots will invest in the
mainland.
</P>
<P>
He said concerned departments in various places in the mainland
have made great efforts to encourage and protect Taiwan investment,
and a specific rule on protecting Taiwanese investment will be
stipulated on the basis of opinions solicited from all circles,
including Taiwan investors.
</P>
<P>
All these measure are taken in the interest of a better
development of cross-straits economic relations, and they favor
investment and business operations of Taiwanese enterpreneurs in
the mainland, he noted.
</P>
<P>
Wan also praised the Taiwanese investors for their help in this
year's flood rescue campaign, saying their deeds just reflect the
brotherly affection of Chinese people all over the world.  
</P>
</TEXT>
