<HEADLINE> Chinese Vice-Premier Meets Taiwan Entrepreneurs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 28 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-Premier Qian
Qichen met here today with presidents of associations of
Taiwan-funded enterprises in the mainland and expressed greetings
for the upcoming Moon Festival.
</P>
<P>
Qian said Taiwan-funded enterprises in the mainland have
scored remarkable achievements in the past decade, and the
mainland now has more than 30,000 Taiwan-funded enterprises.
</P>
<P>
He noted that economic cooperation between the two sides of the
Taiwan Straits complies with the long-term interests of
compatriots on both sides, and that cooperation will be for mutual
benefit.
</P>
<P>
Referring to the Asian financial turmoil and the enormous
floods this year, Qian said the mainland maintained a rapid
economic growth because of the effective measures taken by the
Chinese Communist Party Central Committee and the State Council.
</P>
<P>
At present, the Chinese mainland remains the second hottest
country for investment in the world, and cross-straits economic
exchanges have also brought good opportunities for the Taiwan
investors, he noted.
</P>
<P>
Qian emphasized that the central government will not change its
policy of encouraging Taiwanese investment in the mainland and
will protect all legitimate rights and interests of Taiwanese
investors.
</P>
<P>
He voiced the hope that the associations of Taiwan-funded
enterprises in various places of the mainland will frankly
exchange views with concerned local departments on problems
encountered by Taiwanese investors in order to solve them
properly.  
