<HEADLINE> Russia Looks Forward to Continued Cooperation With Germany </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, September 28 (Xinhua) -- Russia hopes the new German
government under Gerhard Shroeder "will continue to strengthen
relations and pursue a policy of neighborliness, partnership and
mutual trust" with Moscow, Foreign Ministry spokesman Vladimir
Rakhmanin said.
</P>
<P>
"This reflects the interests of our peoples and the goal of
international peace, European security and stability," the
Interfax news agency quoted Rakhmanin as saying.
</P>
<P>
He said the two neighbors should try to "avoid pauses in
Russian-German cooperation despite the current effort shape
governments in both countries."
</P>
<P>
Russian Prime Minister Yevgeny Primakov, who took office more
than two weeks ago, is still struggling to form a broad-based
cabinet.
</P>
<P>
Rakhmanin praised Shroeder's Social-Democratic Party, which won
40.9 percent of votes in Sunday's general elections, as "one of
the oldest and most authoritative democratic parties in Europe."
He also noted that Russia's contacts with its leaders "were
established a long time ago."
</P>
<P>
He also commended German leader Helmut Kohl's "outstanding
role in the history of Germany and Europe at one of the most
crucial stages in their history.
</P>
<P>
"Over the past few years Russia and Germany have created a
weighty potential for comprehensive and fruitful cooperation,"
Rakhmanin said. 
</P>
