<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EC Chief Congratulates Schroeder over Victory </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, September 28 (Xinhua) -- European Commission
President Jacques Santer extended on Monday his congratulation to
Gerhard Schroeder over his victory in the German general election.
</P>
<P>
Santer said in a written statement that he congratulated the
German chancellor-elect on his clear victory in the parliamentary
election on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Schroeder's Social-Democratic Party defeated Chancellor Helmut
Kohl's Christian Democratic Union in the election.
</P>
<P>
Santer described the outgoing chancellor as one of those who
were vital to the development of the European economic and
monetary union, and the single currency.
</P>
<P>
He said: "Schroeder now takes over in this relay race and I am
sure that Chancellor Schroeder will play his role as the driving
force behind the construction of Europe."
</P>
<P>
The commission chief praised Schroeder's Social-Democratic
Party as always pro-European.
</P>
<P>
The Social-Democratic Party has reportedly entered into talks
with the Green Party in an effort to build Germany's first
center-left coalition government in 16 years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
