<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Troops Kill 194 Rebels in Battle in Northern SriLanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, September 28 (Xinhua) -- At least 194 Tamil rebels and
43 soldiers were killed in a fierce battle between government
troops and the Tamil rebels in the Northern Province of Sri Lanka
Sunday, according to a news release issued Monday.
</P>
<P>
The release from the Defense Ministry said at least 194 of the
rebel cadres were killed and a large number of rebels wounded in
the confrontation which took place south of Paranthan in
Kilinochchi.
</P>
<P>
A total of 43 government troops were killed and 110 others
wounded during the battle, the release said.
</P>
<P>
The Tamil rebels have been waging a war for a separate state in
the north and east of the country since 1983. 
</P>
</TEXT>
