<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Baoshan Iron, Steel Group Buys Into Two Smaller Firms </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, September 28 (Xinhua) -- The Shanghai-based Baoshan
Iron and Steel Group will now control 60 percent of Yichang Light
Gauge Sheet Co. Ltd. and its subsidiary Yichang Tin-Coating Sheet
Co. Ltd., said a spokesman from the Baoshan Group today.
</P>
<P>
According to the spokesman, the group will also help reorganize
the two companies in a move that is a prelude to a major alliance
the Group will forge with local iron and steel companies.
</P>
<P>
Yichang Light Gauge Sheet Co. Ltd., an important Shanghai
industrial project, has produced and sold 1.33 million tons of
cold-rolled light gauge sheets since May of 1991, when the company
began production, to late 1997. The company has also paid 648
million yuan in taxes during that period.
</P>
<P>
In 1994, the company created a new firm with imported
production lines to produce electrolytic tin coating sheet widely
used in food and other can-making industries. The subsidiary
company has a designed annual production capacity of 100,000 tons.
</P>
<P>
After the assets reshuffle, Yichang Light Gauge Sheet
Co. Ltd. and its subsidiary, Yichang Tin Coating Sheet Co. Ltd
will be jointly operated by Baoshan Iron and Steel Group and five
other companies.
</P>
<P>
The corporate spokesman added that Baoshan will make good use
of its advantages in qualified personnel, management expertise,
technologies and capital to improve Yichang's asset-debt
structure, upgrade equipment, improve product quality of Yichang
companies, realize an optimized distribution of resources and
eventually improve economic benefits.  
</P>
</TEXT>
