<HEADLINE> Central China City Begins Airport Expansion </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, September 28 (Xinhua) -- Changsha, capital of
central China's Hunan Province, began expanding its Huanghua
International Airport today.
</P>
<P>
The new airport lounge, at a cost of 390 million yuan, will
open on October 1, 2000, with the capacity to handle four million
passengers a year, twice as many as now.
</P>
<P>
Huanghua International was built ten years ago with a floor
space of 7,400 square meters, now insufficient for the rapidly
increasing number of passengers.
</P>
<P>
A city official said that the expansion, together with some
other projects, has received 20 billion in infrastructure
investment from the central and local governments since the region
was hit by heavy flooding this summer, and that the expanded
facility, once completed, will promote the regional
economy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
