<HEADLINE> Spain-Hong Kong Trade Remains Robust </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 28 (Xinhua) -- Total trade volume between
Hong Kong and Spain for the first half of this year came to 1.1
billion U.S. dollars, according to an announcement of the Spanish
Trade Commission in Hong Kong Monday.
</P>
<P>
The results indicate that Spain should still see increases in
trade in some segments this year even amid Asian economic
downturn, the announcement said.
</P>
<P>
The overall figure for Spain's exports to Hong Kong soared by
about 70 percent during the first half of 1998 to hit 478 million
U.S. dollars (about 3.6 million HK dollars), the announcement said.
</P>
<P>
The announcement said Spanish manufacturers are maintaining
investment and confidence in the important Asian market.
</P>
<P>
Next week Spain will show its strong presence at two large
scale exhibitions, the Asia Pacific Leather Fair (October 5-7) and
the Cosmoprof Asia (October 6-8), at the Hong Kong Convention and
Exhibition Center.
</P>
<P>
Ernesto Tejedor, Spain's trade commissioner in Hong Kong, said
Spain is continuing its investment in the very important Asian
market.
</P>
<P>
"Overall trade results are pleasing and we are seeing a
long-term approach bringing rewards in this vast marketplace," he
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
