<HEADLINE> Shots Fired at Israeli Students in Hebron </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, September 28 (Xinhua) -- Shots were fired on Monday
at a group of Israeli students in the West Bank city of Hebron,
injuring one girl student, Israel Radio reported.
</P>
<P>
The Israeli students were headed toward the Jewish enclave of
Tel Rumeida in the center of the city when shots were fired at
them from the Palestinian-controlled part of the city and the
female student was wounded in the leg, the Radio said.
</P>
<P>
Hebron is the Palestinian controlled city in the southern part
of the West Bank with a population of about 130,000. But in the
city, about 450 Jewish settlers are living at Tel Rumeida and
other areas with the protection of the Israeli Defense Force
(IDF).
</P>
<P>
Tensions between the Jewish settlers and local Palestinians in
the city rose considerably last month after 63-year-old Jewish
settler Rabbi Shlmon Ra'anan was stabbed to death at his home in
Tei Rumeida.
</P>
<P>
Following the incident, the IDF imposed a curfew around the
areas inhabited by the Jewish settlers and a closure of the city,
bringing the shortage of water and food and other hardships to the
Palestinians in the city
</P>
<P>
Two weeks ago, Israeli security forces raided the house of two
Hamas (Islamic Resistance Movement) members Adel Awadallah
brothers near Hebron, killing all of them.
</P>
<P>
Following this incident, Hamas spiritual leader Sheikh Yassin
ordered the Hamas' military wing Izzadin-Kassam to hit Israeli
targets at appropriate times. 
</P>
</TEXT>
