<DOCNO> XIE19980928.0100 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> C'wealth Tax Conf Opens in Uganda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, September 28 (Xinhua) -- The 19th technical
conference of the Commonwealth Association of Tax Administrators
(CATA) opens here Monday morning with improvement of tax
administration as its key theme.
</P>
<P>
The five-day conference, which drew hundreds of delegates from
32 of the 45 CATA members, was officially opened by Ugandan Prime
Minister Kintu Musoke.
</P>
<P>
Musoke extended a warm welcome to the delegates and pledged
full support from the Ugandan government for the CATA work so
that its resolutions can be implemented as soon as possible.
</P>
<P>
He noted that over the past 10 years, Uganda has focused on
stabilizing and liberalizing its macro-economy, benefiting much
from the forum CATA provides for exchange of ideas and
information.
</P>
<P>
CATA was formed by the Commonwealth Finance Ministers meeting
held in Barbados in 1977. Its aim is to promote and encourage
excellency in tax administration by providing technical support
through training and manpower development, enabling closer
cooperation in this field, harmonizing and modernizing tax
systems.
</P>
<P>
It organizes seminars and workshops for senior tax officers,
collecting, analyzing and disseminating information on tax
administrators as well as carrying out functions related to the
overall improvement of their capabilities.
</P>
<P>
Uganda is the fourth African country to host CATA after
Nigeria (1992), Tanzania (1994) and Zimbabwe (1996). 
</P>
</TEXT>
