<HEADLINE> Premier Urges Fulfilment of New Tasks, Goals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 28 (Xinhua) -- Chinese premier Zhu Rongji
has urged governments in flood-stricken regions to do their best
in helping flood victims put their life on track and ensure they
survive the coming winter.
</P>
<P>
Following president Jiang Zemin's keynote speech at the
national meeting on reviewing the anti-flood efforts and
commendation of anti-flood heros, the premier said the tasks and
goals in the immediate future illustrated in the president's
speech represent another major strategy of the Chinese Communist
Party Central Committee and must be carried out in an earnest
manner.
</P>
<P>
Zhu said one of the concrete steps to carry on the heroic spirit
demonstrated in the anti-flood and rescue efforts is to do a good
job in disaster relief work.
</P>
<P>
Apart from meeting the daily needs of the flood victims,
efforts must be made to repair damaged farmland, water conservancy
facilities and infrastructures.
</P>
<P>
In resuming industrial production, priorities should be given to
optimize structures and improve quality; and in rebuilding
flood-devastated areas, attention should be paid to work out
overall and long-term development plan, with a view to building up
effective flood-control facilities, Zhu said.
</P>
<P>
He urged the whole country to work diligently in the remaining
three months of the year to strive for the realization of economic
goals projected for 1998.
</P>
<P>
Zhu presided over today's meeting which was held by the CPC
Central Committee and the State Council. Top Party and state
leaders attended the meeting at the Great Hall of the People along
with some 10,000 people. 
</P>
