<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- Hurricane Georges struck the coast areas of the
Gulf of Mexico Sunday, bringing high wind and heavy rain that
drove thousands of people in southern Alabama, Mississippi and
Luisiana into shelters, reports reaching here said.
</P>
<P>
The hurricane stirred up seven-meter-high waves that clipped
off fishing piers along Alabama's coast, smashing over concrete
walls to demolish a fishing pier. Georges was moving
north-northwest. The National Hurricane Center said that the
hurricane's center was expected to reach the Gulf Coast on
Monday. (US-Hurricane)
</P>
