- - - -
</P>
<P>
ZAGREB -- Visiting U.S. Defense Secretary William Cohen said
Sunday that the North Atlantic Treaty Organization (NATO) will be
forced to take action in Kosovo if Yugoslavia does not take the
U.N. warning.
</P>
<P>
Cohen, who traveled to Bosnia-Herzegovina from Macedonia, told
reporters in Sarajevo that NATO is drawing up plans for actions by
air. According to Cohen, the international community wished to see
an early end to the Kosovo conflicts, which would enable the
return of a large number of refugees, and called for negotiations
between the Yugoslav authorities and the Kosovo Liberation Army
which fights for the independence of Kosovo. (Cohen-Kosovo)
