<HEADLINE> Beijing Gathering Marks Victory of Flood Fighting (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 28 (Xinhua) -- Some 10,000 people gathered
in the Great Hall of the People in downtown Beijing this afternoon
to review the just-concluded national anti-flood and rescue
operation and commend those who made outstanding contributions to
the victory of the two-month-long fight against the worst flooding
in decades in the country.
</P>
<P>
The meeting was jointly held by the Chinese Communist Party
(CPC) Central Committee and the State Council.
</P>
<P>
Top Party and government leaders including President Jiang
Zemin, Li Peng, Zhu Rongji, Li Ruihuan, Hu Jintao and Li Lanqing
attended the meeting, along with leading officials from Party and
government departments, mass organizations, and all provincial,
regional and municipal governments.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the meeting, Jiang, also general secretary of the
CPC Central Committee and chairman of the Central Military
Commission, noted that the flood fighting and disaster relief in
China has been crowned with a complete victory, and it marked
another great achievement of the Chinese people that attracted
worldwide attention.
</P>
<P>
"The victory of our fight against the floods once again proves
that the leadership by the CPC is essential if we are to overcome
difficulties and risks on the road ahead, achieve prosperity and
rejuvenation of our nation and bring well-being to our people,"
Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
He also spoke highly of the people's role in battling the
floods, calling them "the main forces and real heroes" in winning
the final victory.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980928.0127 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Beijing Gathering Marks Victory of Flood Fighting (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Premier Zhu Rongji, who presided over today's conference, said
in his opening speech that the meeting would not only help sum up
the experience of the anti-flood efforts and commend people with
outstanding contributions, but also encourage the entire Chinese
people to carry forward the heroic spirit demonstrated in the face
of the floods, as well as mobilize people in the flooded areas to
work hard in rehabilitating production and rebuilding their homes.
</P>
<P>
Five people representing regions worst hit by the floods, army
forces participating in the flood-fighting and rescue operations
and various political and mass organizations also spoke at the
gathering.
</P>
<P>
The speakers included Jia Zhijie, secretary of the CPC Hubei
Provincial Committee; Xu Youfang, secretary of the CPC
Heilongjiang Provincial committee; Tao Bojun, commander of the
Guangzhou Military Area Command of the Chinese People's Liberation
Army; He Luli, chairwoman of the Central Committee of the
Revolutionary Committee of the Chinese Kuomintang; and Zhang
Dinghua, first secretary of the All-China Federation of Trade
Unions' Secretariat.
</P>
<P>
They agreed that the "great victory" of the battle against
floods should first be attributed to the correct leadership of the
CPC Central Committee with Jiang Zemin at the core.
</P>
<P>
"The Party Central Committee with Comrade Jiang Zemin at the
core has fully displayed their outstanding leading ability with
their right decisions and prompt orders after taking the overall
situation into account," they noted.
</P>
<P>
Also present at today's meeting were representatives from
different localities, including those from the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region. Foreign diplomats and representatives of
international organizations in China attended the meeting upon
invitation.
</P>
<P>
China was hit this summer by the worst flooding in nearly half
a century along the Yangtze River and by floods from the
northeastern Nenjiang and Songhua rivers. The ravaging flood
waters killed 3,004 people and affected 223 million others.
Direct economic losses were estimated at about 20 billion U.S.
dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
