<HEADLINE> Chinese Vice Premier Meets Caribbean Banker </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 28 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice Premier Wen
Jiabao here today met with a Caribbean Development Bank (CDB)
delegation led by its President Sir Neville Nicholls.
</P>
<P>
Wen gave a welcome to Nicholls and his party, saying
that he appreciated CDB's adherence to "One China" policy and
its support to China's admission to CDB.
</P>
<P>
Wen hoped the two sides can further their cooperation on the
basis of mutual benefit.
</P>
<P>
Nicholls also expressed his willingness to enhance the
cooperation between the Caribbean region and China.
</P>
<P>
The two sides also had an exchange of views on East Asia
financial crisis and other issues of common concern.
</P>
<P>
Dai Xianglong, governor of the People's Bank of China, was
present at the meeting. 
</P>
