<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Beijing's Autumn-Winter Clothing And Accessories Fair </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 28 (Xinhua) -- The 1998 China International
Clothing and Accessories Fair will show this year's autumn and
winter collections October 14-17 in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
The autumn and winter collections are expected to show that
China is in line with style and fashion in the world. The spring
and summer show was held in April and resulted in 5 billion yuan
worth of business.
</P>
<P>
The spring and summer collections finally caught up with the
Hong Kong Fashion Week, one of the leading activities of its kind
in Asia, in scale.
</P>
<P>
The fair has been held annually since 1993. It is the largest
of its kind in China. Its purpose is to help give China's garment
industry more publicity for its name-brand products, to promote
Chinese designers, and to help make Beijing a worldwide garment
center. The 1999 China International Clothing and Accessories Fair
is scheduled for March 24-27 in Beijing. 
</P>
</TEXT>
