<DOCNO> XIE19980928.0135 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Foreign Interference to Weaken Malaysian Govt Proved: </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, September 28 (Xinhua) -- Malaysian Information
Minister Mohamed Rahmat said Monday there was proof of foreign
interference to weaken the Malaysian government following the
sacking of its deputy prime minister and finance minister Anwar
Ibrahim.
</P>
<P>
Anwar was sacked on September 2 and was expelled from the
ruling United Malays National Organization (UMNO) a day later for
"low morals".
</P>
<P>
Mohamed said what was being faced now was an internal matter
and Malaysians had the right to solve the problem themselves
without outside interference.
</P>
<P>
Several divisions of the UMNO have been used for the purpose of
toppling Prime Minister Mahathir Mohamad as the party president,
he told reporters Monday in Johor Baharu, about 370 kilometers
south from here, the Malaysian national news agency Bernama
reported.
</P>
<P>
He said that leaders at divisional levels had been paid monthly
allowances of between 5,000 ringgit (1,315 U.S. dollars) and
10,000 ringgit (2,631 U.S. dollars) and some divisions had been
allocated with 1 million ringgit (263,157 U.S. dollars) to 2
million ringgit (526,315 U.S. dollars) to carry out subversive
activities in the UMNO.
</P>
<P>
"We can identify the divisions involved. There is talk that 90
divisions had been used in this way," Mohamed, who is also a
member of the UMNO Supreme Council, was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
"The money they received is to implement programs to topple the
leadership," he said.
</P>
<P>
He urged the leaders of these divisions to repent and return to
the party's struggle.
</P>
<P>
He said the integrity of the UMNO had been challenged and hence
every member should show loyalty to the party and accept with an
open mind the prime minister's decision to sack Anwar Ibrahim from
the government.
</P>
<P>
They (party members) should also accept the UMNO Supreme
Council's decision to expel Anwar from the party as the move was
to preserve the UMNO's cleanliness, Mohamed added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980928.0136 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jiang on People's Role in Flood-fighting (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
At the critical juncture, leading officials at all levels
hurried to the flood sites and fought tenaciously alongside with
soldiers and civilians. Party organizations at grassroots levels
gave full play to the role of the party branch as the political
core and the fighting bastion. Jiang also praised CPC and Youth
League members for their roles as the vanguards and model flood
fighters, saying that they set a very good example for the general
public by being the first to charge ahead and the last to retreat.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that the PLA and the armed police, responding to the
call of the Party and the people resolutely, sent over 300,000
officers and soldiers to plunge into the fight against the
floods. They carried on the revolutionary spirit of fearing
neither hardship nor death and kept up the style of fighting
tirelessly and continuously, and played the role of the backbone.
</P>
<P>
He also praised policemen for their active participation in the
battle against the floods, and contributed a great deal to
safeguarding the social order in flood areas.
</P>
<P>
The president said that in all the areas threatened and hit by
the floods, people did not panic over the surging waves, nor did
they become pessimistic or disheartened over the loss of their
homes and their beloved. Despite their sorrow they braced
themselves up to fight the floods. They preferred to save the
major interests of their homeland at the expense of family
interests and to give up local interests to safeguard the overall
interests of the country, exhibiting a very high level of moral
standard and lofty values.
</P>
<P>
Jiang pointed out that people engaged in water conservancy,
meteorology, hydrology and other scientific-technological fields
worked day and night and played an important role in offering
technical guidance.
</P>
<P>
Medical and health workers coming from all parts of the country
went right to the front lines to prevent epidemics and cure
diseases, thus ensuring good health of flood-fighters.
</P>
<P>
The media people gave timely coverage of the directives of the
CPC Central Committee and the State Council, and went right to the
flood-fighting forefront, despite hardships and dangers, to
popularize the heroic deeds of flood-fighting soldiers and
civilians, promoting what is right and uplifting the fighting will.
</P>
<P>
The president also praised comrades from the
telecommunications, transportation and other sectors who all gave
top priority to supporting flood control, worked in close
coordination and made important contribution in their respective
capacities.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
