<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jiang on People's Role in Flood-fighting (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 28 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin
called today the masses of people are the main forces and real
heros in winning the battle against this year's serious floods in
the country.
</P>
<P>
Jiang, also general secretary of the Central Committee of the
Communist Party of China and chairman of the Central Military
Commission, made the remark at a national conference on the review
and commendation of the flood-fighting and disaster relief efforts
convened in the Great Hall of the People in Beijing this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
The president said that throughout the fight, the CPC Central
Committee, paying close attention to the personal safety and vital
interests of the people in the disaster areas, took direct command
of the battle and always pulled together the flood-fighting
soldiers and civilians with one heart and one mind.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said, since the beginning of flood season, the central
leadership followed closely the climatic changes and the flooding
situation along the rivers and made timely and thoughtful
arrangements for the nationwide flood-fight.
</P>
<P>
In light of the realities in areas under the threat of the
floods, the central government clearly set forth the strategic
policy of taking strict precautions and defending the dykes to the
last to ensure the safety of the Yangtze embankment, the major
cities and people's lives, and made the important policy decision
of deploying large number of PLA men in a concerted fights along
with civilians to conquer the floods, Jiang noted.
</P>
<P>
At the most critical moment, the central government, judging
the hour and sizing up the situation and making the right
judgment, issued a general mobilization order, calling on all the
soldiers and civilians to have full confidence and hold their
position steadfastly till the final victory.
</P>
<P>
The State Flood Control and Drought Relief Headquarters,
unswervingly implementing the policy decision of the CPC Central
Committee and the State Council, made full preparations, overall
arrangements and scientific deployment, gave resolute command and
thus gained the initiative in the flood-fight. These major policy
decisions and their implementation served to guide and ensure the
smooth progress of the flood-fighting and disaster relief work.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that party committees and governments at all levels
in the flood-stricken provinces and regions, in an earnest
effort to enforce the policies and decisions of the CPC Central
Committee and the State Council, strengthened the leadership over
the flood control effort and went all out to make a success of
the work of mobilization and organization.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
