<HEADLINE> Jiang on People's Role in Flood-fighting (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
President Jiang said that people across the country offered
heartfelt support to victims of the flooding. Carrying forward the
Chinese nation's fine tradition of fraternity and mutual help,
they selflessly supported the soldiers and civilians on the front
lines of flood-fighting in an all-round way, he said.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that during the flood-fighting, 1.2 billion people
in China were united as one, from white-haired senior citizens to
children wearing Young Pioneer's red scarves, from workers,
farmers, intellectuals to cadres at all levels.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the Party members and cadres have proved with
deeds that they have deserved the title of honor as members of the
Communist Party and as public servants of the people.
</P>
<P>
The president said that our army have also proved with deeds to
be a revolutionary force that deserves the complete trust of the
Party and the people, and a great wall of steel that safeguards
our national security and the people's interests, and defends our
reform, opening-up and modernization drive. PLA officers and men
are the most beloved people of our times, he said.
</P>
<P>
Jiang stressed that the Chinese people, too, have proved with
deeds that the Chinese people have a glorious tradition of unity
and solidarity, fortitude and hard struggle and that the Chinese
nation has an extraordinary cohesive power.
</P>
<P>
"No difficulty or risk can subdue the Chinese nation", Jiang
said.
</P>
</TEXT>
