<HEADLINE> Jiang on People's Role in Flood-fighting (4) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Jiang said that when we began to carry out reform and opening
up and build a socialist market economy, some people expressed
doubt whether the Chinese nation would abandon its fine tradition,
whether the Chinese people would lose their strong cohesion, and
whether the CPC and the PLA would change their nature and purposes
under the new historical circumstances and with diversified
interests of various social sectors.
</P>
<P>
The great victory in the fight against the floods is another
most telling answer to their question, Jiang said, adding that the
purpose of the CPC has not changed.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that the Party remains committed to serving the
people heart and soul; the political nature of the PLA has not
changed, the PLA is still a revolutionary army under the absolute
leadership of the Party; the Chinese people's adherence to their
fine traditions has not changed. These have not, will not and
shall never be changed.
</P>
<P>
"With such a Party, such an army and such a people, we can
create miracles in the world," he stressed.
</P>
<P>
The extremely hard and bitter struggle against the floods, the
severe test of life and death, and the experience of braving the
wind and storm together have strengthened the flesh-and-blood
ties between the Party and the masses, and the fish-and-water
relationship between the army and the people, and reinforced the
solidarity of all our ethnic groups to an unprecedented level,
Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
"We should all the more cherish and always carry on such
extremely valuable ideological and political assets," he said.
</P>
