<HEADLINE> Anti-flood Victory Testifies To Party Leadership Effectiveness: President  (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Beijing, September 28 (Xinhua) -- Party General Secretary and
President Jiang Zemin has urged to uphold the leadership of the
Communist Party of China (CPC) which has been proved effective and
decisive in achieving the anti-flood efforts in summer this year.
</P>
<P>
"The victory of our fight against the floods once again proves
that the leadership by the CPC is essential if we are to overcome
difficulties and risks on the road ahead, achieve prosperity and
rejuvenation of our nation and bring well-being to our people,"
Jiang told some 10,000 people attending the grand meeting held in
Beijing this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said the CPC has the whole-hearted support of the people
and enjoys a high prestige among them and has a strong rallying
power.
</P>
<P>
With the CPC as the leading core of the country, the Chinese
people have been organized to an unprecedentedly high extent and
their extraordinary creativity to transform the society and
exploit the nature has also been greatly enhanced, he said.
</P>
<P>
Over the years, the Party has united with and led the entire
Chinese people to overcome one difficulty after another and
achieve success after success, he noted. In the late 1980s and
early 1990s, China stood up to the international and domestic
political disturbances to defend the great undertaking of building
socialism with Chinese characteristics, and successfully withstood
a severe test of a political risk.
</P>
<P>
Since last year, China has taken effective measures to deal
with the impact of the East Asian financial crisis with composure,
pressed ahead with our reform, opening-up and modernization drive,
and successfully withstood a severe test of economic risks.
</P>
<P>
This time the country conquered the assaults of the
extraordinarily serious flooding, maintained the overall social
stability and economic growth of the whole country, and withstood
a severe test of natural disaster.
</P>
<P>
"Working side by side and adhering to the leadership of the
CPC, we will surely be able to address all possible complex
situations calmly and overcome all the difficulties or hardships
that might crop up on the way ahead," the president said.
</P>
</TEXT>
