<HEADLINE> Anti-Flood Victory Testifies to Party Leadership Effectiveness: President (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The president said the victory shows that China's socialist
system has tremendous advantages. Under the socialist system, he
added, efforts and resources can be mobilized to concentrate on
one major undertaking at a time and the people mobilized and
organized to score significant achievements one after another.
</P>
<P>
During the fight against the floods, all localities and all
departments across China brought into play the spirit of great
unity and close cooperation, as evidenced by the fact that when
one place was in difficulty, help came from all other places and
that all activities of the country were well coordinated just like
moves in a game of chess.
</P>
<P>
They all had their own local and immediate interests
subordinated to the overall and long-term interests, thus
unleashing an enormous and unparalleled force, he noted.
</P>
<P>
The victory tells us once again that the people, and the people
alone are the genuine driving force in the making of history. The
people are the inexhaustible source of strength of all our
undertakings.
</P>
<P>
"Like all the previous historic victories, the victory in the
fight against the floods is, in the final analysis, a victory of
the people," the president noted.
</P>
<P>
"Once again, the Chinese people have demonstrated the valuable
spirit of helping each other through thick and thin. Once again,
the Chinese nation has demonstrated the heroic courage to work
unremittingly through self-reliance. All the descendants of the
Yan and Huang emperors feel the greatest pride and highest honor
in having such spirit and courage."
</P>
<P>
The victory in the fight against the floods is a great victory
in our persistent endeavor of the reform, opening-up and
modernization drive.
</P>
<P>
Therefore, the only path towards accelerated socialist
modernization in China is to adhere to reforms and opening-up, to
constantly expand overseas exchanges and cooperation, and to
earnestly learn from and draw upon all the fine fruits of human
civilization as well as any useful experience that is beneficial
to our economic growth and social progress, Jiang said.  
</P>
