<HEADLINE> Jiang Zemin Calls for Completing Tasks of This Year (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 28 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin
today called on the Party and the entire nation to develop the
great flood-fighting spirit and work hard with an enterprising
style to resolve problems that may arise on the way ahead and
complete this year's tasks of reform and development with full
confidence.
</P>
<P>
At the National Conference on Review and Commendation of Flood
Fighting and Disaster Relief Endeavor held here today, Jiang urged
the people in the flood-stricken areas to do a good job of
providing disaster relief, rehabilitating production and
rebuilding their homeland.
</P>
<P>
Jiang, also general secretary of the CPC Central Committee and
chairman of the Central Military Commission, said that the Party
committees and governments at all levels in these areas should
give top priority to these tasks.
</P>
<P>
He said that they should work out a practical comprehensive
plan on the basis of rational assessment.
</P>
<P>
It is imperative to carry out the disaster relief work in an
all-round way and to accomplish the tasks of production
resumption and homeland reconstruction on the principle of taking
care of both production and the basic needs of life, removing both
the immediate and root causes of the floods and considering both
the short-term and long-term interests, he said.
</P>
