<HEADLINE> Jiang Zemin Calls for Completing Tasks of This Year (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Jiang said, "We should take good care of the livelihood of
people in the flood-hit areas and always have their interests at
heart. The pressing task now is to ensure a safe winter for people
in these areas."
</P>
<P>
He said that an early resumption and development of production
and an all-out effort for the successful prevention of diseases
and major epidemics are the key to the final success of flood
relief.
</P>
<P>
People should be organized to repair and rebuild the farmlands
ruined by the floods and resume planting, animal husbandry and
aquatic products industry at an earlier date so as to minimize the
damages done to agriculture, he said.
</P>
<P>
"We should restore electricity, telecommunications,
transportation and other infrastructure facilities as soon as
possible," he said, adding that in resuming industrial production,
it is important to organize production in light of the market
demand and make necessary structural readjustments so as to make
new progress.
</P>
<P>
"We should take into account all factors and make overall
arrangements for the people in the flood-stricken areas to rebuild
a lovely homeland at an early date," he said.
</P>
<P>
"All localities in China should give vigorous support to the
restoration and reconstruction work in the disaster areas. Cadres
and people in those areas should continue to carry forward the
spirit of perseverance, enthusiasm and death-defiance, a spirit
they exhibited in the fight against the floods, work hard with
their wisdom and strength to make new achievements in their
economic development and social progress," he said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
