<DOCNO> XIE19980928.0155 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Never Slacken Vigilance against Floods: President Jiang (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 28 (Xinhua) -- Floods have always been a
serious hidden threat to the Chinese nation. The whole Party and
the nation should never slacken their vigilance against them,
Chinese president Jiang Zemin said here today.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the National Conference on Review and Commendation
of Flood Fighting and Disaster Relief Endeavor here this
afternoon, Jiang said that this year's floods have inflicted great
losses and we have paid a heavy price.
</P>
<P>
Natural disaster itself is a bad thing, but it can help people
deepen their understanding of the law of nature in their fight
against it and draw useful conclusions from it. When this is done,
they will be able to make the nature serve their life and social
progress, the president said.
</P>
<P>
"We should seriously sum up the experience in the recent flood
fighting efforts. We should deepen our understanding of the
importance of further improving our ability to ward off natural
disasters, more vigorously pursuing economic development and
social progress, and making more scientific and rational planning
and arrangements," he noted.
</P>
<P>
This is a very important job and the Party and the nation must
seize time to accomplish it, he added.
</P>
<P>
More than a hundred years ago, Frederick Engels pointed out
that mankind could make the nature serve its purpose and control
the nature by changing it, Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
"But in every step we take, we should bear in mind that
mankind can not govern the nature outside the nature. All our
ability to control the nature lies in our understanding and
correct application of the law of nature," he stressed.
</P>
<P>
He said that the people can not have an instant comprehensive
understanding of the law of nature. All laws can be clearly
recognized and cognized by people only after a certain phenomenon
repeats itself numerous times.
</P>
<P>
What was not cognized by people in the past can be understood
today, he said, adding that what we do not understand today will
be understood in the future, and what is important is that we must
try to understand the law of nature, correctly manage it and
learn to follow it to facilitate our economic development and
other social undertakings and obtain a coordinated development of
the economy and ecological environment.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980928.0156 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Never Slacken Vigilance against Floods: President Jiang (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Jiang pointed out that since the founding of New China, the
Party and the country have all along attached importance to the
prevention of and fight against natural disasters. They have led
and organized people in water-conservancy work to harness rivers
and lakes, in large-scale afforestation and water and soil
conservation programs and in the building of flood-control
facilities.
</P>
<P>
All this work which we had done over a long period of time
played an important role in our fight against the floods this
year, according to the president.
</P>
<P>
"But generally speaking, our ability to prevent and fight
floods is still inadequate and there are still many problems in
water-conservancy work and comprehensive harnessing program. All
these problems call for urgent solution," he noted.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that this year's big floods were mainly due to the
unusual climate and a high concentration of rainfall. That is to
say, it was primarily a natural disaster. Needless to say, we
should face squarely such problems as severe ecological
deterioration, the silting up of rivers and lakes and inadequate
water-conservancy facilities, earnestly sum up experience and
lessons and work out practical and effective measures to better
prepare ourselves against natural disasters and more effectively
mitigate possible damages done by such disasters.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said the Central Government has outlined the general
objectives for improving ecological environment and
water-conservancy construction, and the State Council has already
drawn up a detailed plan for that. All localities and departments
should, according to their own conditions, make prompt arrangements
for achieving these objectives with priority given to effectively
improving the ecological environment, harnessing lakes and rivers
and building flood-control and water-conservancy projects.
</P>
<P>
"In a word, the basic purpose is to develop our capacity for
flood control fundamentally through a comprehensive harnessing
program," he concluded. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980928.0157 </DOCNO>
