<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Representatives Attribute Flood Victory to CPC Central Committee (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 28 (Xinhua) -- The Central Committee of the
Communist Party of China (CPC) with Jiang Zemin at the core were
credited by several representatives of people from all over China
with the "great victory" in the fight against the two months of
flooding in China this year.
</P>
<P>
Representatives of five flooded provinces along the Yangtze
River and two provinces and one autonomous region in the North,
military officers and enlisted personnel who participated in the
disaster-relief efforts, and representatives of various political
and social organizations spoke at a grand gathering today to
celebrate the victory.
</P>
<P>
They were: Party chief of Hubei Province Jia Zhijie, Party
chief of Heilongjiang Province Xu Youfang, Commander of the
Guangzhou Military Area Command of the Chinese People's Liberation
Army (PLA) Tao Bojun, Chairman of the Central Revolutionary
Committee of the Chinese Kuomintang He Luli, and First Secretary of
the All-China Federation of Trade Unions Secretariat Zhang Dinghua.
</P>
<P>
The CPC Central Committee and Jiang Zemin have shown their
outstanding leadership ability by making the correct decisions and
giving prompt orders, these representatives said.
</P>
<P>
President Jiang was credited with the fundmental guidelines for
the military and civilians along the Yangtze River and the "do or
die" command at the beginning of the flood fight.
</P>
<P>
At crucial moments, Jiang went to dykes along the river himself
to inspect the situation and offer further guidance.
</P>
<P>
The fight against the floods also reflects the unity of the
military and the people, He Luli said, pointing to officers and
men alike who gave no thought to their own safety when rescuing
others, to flood victims who were willing to sacrifice their own
interests for the interest of the whole, and people in other areas
who made generous donations to the victims.
</P>
