<HEADLINE> Jiang Calls Victory Over Floods Great Achievement of Chinese People (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 28 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin
said here today that the flood fighting and disaster relief in
China has been crowned with a complete victory, and it marked yet
another great achievement of the Chinese people that attracted
world-wide attention.
</P>
<P>
Jiang, who is also general secretary of the Central Committee
of the Communist Party of China (CPC) and chairman of the Central
Military Commission, made the remark at a national conference on
reviewing and commendation of flood fighting and disaster relief
endeavor convened in the Great Hall of the People here this
afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that in the past several months, the Chinese people
waged a mighty and courageous fight against the serious floods
rarely seen in China's history, demonstrating their daring spirit
of heroism.
</P>
<P>
On behalf of the CPC Central Committee, the State Council and
the Central Military Commission, and also on behalf of the whole
Party, the whole army and the people of all ethnic groups in
China, Jiang paid high tribute to the vast numbers of cadres
and the masses of people, to the officers and soldiers of the
People's Liberation Army (PLA), officers and men of the armed
police, policemen, scientists and technicians, medical workers and
journalists, and all the people who fought on the very front
lines in the flood control and disaster relief efforts.
</P>
<P>
Jiang also expressed his heartfelt thanks to the broad ranks
of cadres and people on various fronts, to the democratic
parties, the All-China Federation of Industry and Commerce,
non-party personages and mass organizations who rendered
vigorous assistance to the affected areas as well as people from
all walks of life in the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region,
compatriots in Macao and Taiwan and overseas compatriots and
people of Chinese origin around the world, who were active in
providing assistance to the flooded areas.
