<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jiang Calls Victory over Floods Great Achievement of Chinese People  (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
He pointed out at this very moment, we should express our deep
longing for and profound condolences to the martyrs who sacrificed
their lives in the battle against the floods and to our fellow
countrymen who died in the disaster.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that the flood season this year started with
abnormal weather, which obviously brought about too much rain to
most regions in China and continuous heavy rain to some regions,
thus doubling and redoubling the volume of rainfall which lead to
serious floods in some areas.
</P>
<P>
He continued, the whole Yangtze River valley was hit by another
serious flood this year following the one that happened in 1954,
with eight flood crests appearing successively. For a long period
of time, the water levels exceeded historical records along the
360-km-long Yangtze River section starting downward from Yichang
city and in the Dongting and Boyang lakes, and the water in the
Shashi city section of the Yangtze River once reached a high level
of 45.22 meters.
</P>
<P>
Record-breaking serious floods also hit the Nenjiang River and
Songhua River valley, with three flood crests appearing
successively. For some time, the Xijiang River, a tributary in
the Pearl River valley, and the Minjiang River in east China's
Fujian Province also experienced serious floods.
</P>
<P>
In numerous cities and vast stretches of the rural areas along
the rivers or around the lakes in Hubei, Hunan, Jiangxi, Anhui,
Jiangsu, Heilongjiang and Jilin provinces and the Inner Mongolia
Autonomous Region, the economic and social development and the
safety of people's lives and property all came under the threats
from serious floods, Jiang said.
</P>
</TEXT>
