<HEADLINE> Jiang Calls Victory over Floods Great Achievement of Chinese People (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Jiang pointed out that to conquer the floods resolutely was a
major struggle aimed at protecting the safety of people's lives
and property and defending the achievements of China's reform,
opening-up and modernization drive. It was also a rigorous test on
the courage, confidence and strength of the Chinese people in
combating natural disasters.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that under the leadership of the CPC Central
Committee, the entire Party, army and the people took swift and
urgent action against the flood. He said that the vast numbers of
cadres and the broad masses of people in the flood-stricken
provinces and regions, in particular, joined forces with the
officers and men of the PLA and the armed police, who came to
their assistance, in a vigorous, stirring, life-and-death battle
to repel the floods and turn the tide.
</P>
<P>
Eventually they succeeded in ensuring the safety of the main
embankments along the major rivers and lakes, the key cities, the
transport trunk lines, and people's lives and property, thereby
bringing down to the minimum the losses caused by this
extraordinary natural disaster. Jiang called it a remarkable great
achievement.
</P>
<P>
The president said that our people, our people's armed forces,
and the vast numbers of our Party and cadres added a new and
splendid chapter to the annals of progress of the Chinese nation
with their heroic action. It will go down in history as a
magnificent feat in mankind's fight against natural disasters.
</P>
