<HEADLINE> Zambia to Phase Out Telex Service </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, September 28 (Xinhua) -- Telex service will be phased
out in Zambia as the global computer problem by the year 2000 is
becoming a reality in the country, Zambia Telecommunications
Company (ZAMTEL) has announced.
</P>
<P>
ZAMTEL said in a circular issued to its customers lately that
the company has decided to phase out the telex service as a
precautionary measure to the year 2000 millennium computer
threat.
</P>
<P>
The circular advised its customers to acquire more fax and
telephone lines which are cheaper for the company to maintain in
view of the year 2000 computer problem.
</P>
<P>
Times of Zambia Monday quoted ZAMTEL as saying that those who
continue using telex service will be charged for economic fees.
</P>
<P>
The Zambian Ministry of Communications and Transport has set
up a national task force to deal with issues relating to the year
2000 problem, also known as millennium bug. 
</P>
</TEXT>
