<P>
The spokesman denied a report that Botswana would deploy 400
more troops in Lesotho, said the report.
</P>
<P>
He also said Botswana army chief Lieutenant-General Ian Khama
would also join other regional defense ministers in Lesotho's
capital Maseru Monday morning to review the progress of the
restoration of law and order to the tiny mountainous kingdom.
</P>
<P>
About 1,000 troops from South Africa and Botswana had been
deployed in Lesotho since September 22 to help the Lesotho
government to restore law and stability in the country.
</P>
<P>
On Sunday, Botswanan Foreign Minister Mompati Merafhe said in
Maseru that his country, together with South Africa and Zimbabwe,
would be the guarantors of peace and stability in Lesotho, and
the Botswanan troops would stay in the kingdom until their
mission is achieved. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
