to nine months in prison for her failing to prevent the
assassination of former Israeli Prime Minister Yitzhak Rabin by
her friend Yigal Amir. She also received a 15-month suspended
sentence. Har Shefi had been convicted in June after
acknowledging that Amir had boasted to her of his intentions to
assassinate Rabin.
</P>
<P>
Yediot Aharonot:
</P>
<P>
-- About 70 people were injured on Sunday in clashes between
Israeli-Arabs and police in a northern town of Israel. The clashes
broke out as police tried to disperse the Arab protesters, who
were staging a sit-in on a plot of land the army has
confiscated. Twenty protesters were also arrested during the
confrontation. 
