<HEADLINE> Jiang Delivers Important Speech on Flood-fighting Victory </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 28 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin
said here today that the flood fighting and disaster relief in
China has been crowned with a complete victory, and it marked yet
another great achievement of the Chinese people that attracted
world-wide attention.
</P>
<P>
Jiang, who is also general secretary of the Central Committee
of the Communist Party of China (CPC) and chairman of the Central
Military Commission, is delivering a speech at a national
conference on reviewing and commendation of flood fighting and
disaster relieving endeavor being convened in the Great Hall of
the People.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that in the past several months, the Chinese people
waged a mighty and courageous fight against the serious floods
rarely seen in China's history, demonstrating their daring spirit
of heroism.
</P>
<P>
About 10,000 people are gathering in the Great Hall of the
People this afternoon to review the just-concluded national
anti-flood and rescue operation and commend those who have made
outstanding contributions to the victory over the two-month-long
fighting against the worst flooding in decades in the country.
</P>
