<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Beijing Grand Meeting to Commend Anti-flood Heroes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 28 (Xinhua) -- The Communist Party of China
(CPC) Central Committee and the State Council are holding a grand
meeting here at 3:00 p.m. today to review the recent nationwide
flood-fighting efforts and to commend those who contributed
tremendously to the victory over the disaster.
</P>
<P>
President Jiang Zemin, who is also general secretary of the CPC
Central Committee and chairman of the Central Military Commission,
is going to address the meeting in the Great Hall of the People,
which is being attended by approximately 10,000 people across the
country.
</P>
<P>
China suffered devastating floods for decades along the Yangtze
River and from floods on the Nengjiang and Songhua rivers in
northeast China this summer. The ravaging floodwater took 3,004
lives and affected another 2.3 million nationwide. Direct economic
losses were estimated at about 20 billion US dollars.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
