<DOCNO> XIE19980928.0190 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Grand Meeting to Commend Anti-flood Heros </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 28 (Xinhua) -- About 10,000 people are
gathering in the Great Hall of the People this afternoon to review
the just-concluded national anti-flood and rescue operation and
commend those who have made outstanding contributions to the
victory over the two-month-long fighting against the worst
flooding in decades in the country.
</P>
<P>
Premier Zhu Rongji presided over the meeting which is being
held by the Chinese Communist Party Central Committee and the
State Council.
</P>
<P>
Top Party and government leaders including Jiang Zemin, Li
Peng, Li Ruihuan, Hu Jintao and Li Lanqing attended the meeting,
along with leading officials from Party and government
departments, mass organizations, provincial, regional and
municipal governments.
</P>
<P>
Also present at the meeting were representatives from different
localities, including those from the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region. Some foreign diplomats and international
organization representatives in China were invited to the meeting.
</P>
<P>
In his opening speech, Premier Zhu said the Chinese people,
under the leadership of the Central Party Committee, waged an
arduous struggle against the worst flooding of the country this
summer.
</P>
<P>
"Heart-stirring deeds and anti-flood heros emerged in large
numbers during the flood-fighting and rescue operation, and they
fully demonstrated the close ties between the Party and the
people, between officials and the rank and file, and between the
people's army and the civilians," said Zhu.
</P>
<P>
While summing up the experience of the anti-flood efforts and
commending the outstanding figures, the meeting will encourage
people of the whole country to carry out the heroic spirit
demonstrated in the anti-flood efforts, mobilize people in the
disastrous areas to work diligently in rehabilitating production
and rebuilding their homeland, Zhu noted.
</P>
<P>
The premier called on the whole country to rally around the
Central Party Committee headed by Jiang Zemin, further advance
the causes of reform and opening-up and do a good job in all
fronts.
</P>
<P>
China was hit by the worst flooding in recent 45 years along
the Yangtze River and floods from the Nenjiang and Songhua rivers
in northeastern China this summer. The ravaging floodwaters killed
3,004 people and affected another 2.3 million. Direct economic
losses were estimated at about 20 billion US dollars.  
</P>
</TEXT>
