<HEADLINE> New Zealand Stocks Finish Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, September 28 (Xinhua) -- The New Zealand share
market closed higher here Monday.
</P>
<P>
The NZSE40 Index ended 7 points higher at 1,717 with a turnover
of 60 million NZ dollars (29.9 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Among the major leaders, AMP was the biggest winner, rising 10
cents to 2,535 cents. Telecom gained 8 cents to 752 cents.
Auckland Airport and Carter Holt Harvey put on 2 cents each to 185
cents and 133 cents respectively. Brierley Investments edged up 1
cent to 35 cents.
</P>
<P>
Air New Zealand and Fletcher Paper were stable at 143 cents
and 100 cents respectively.
</P>
<P>
Fletcher Energy lost 6 cents to 298 cents, Fletcher Building 5
cents to 193 cents, and Fletcher Forest 2 cents to 43 cents.
</P>
</TEXT>
