<BODY>
<HEADLINE>   Over 5,000 Girls Involved in Sex Work in Nepal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, September 28 (Xinhua) -- More than 5,000 girls are
involved in sex work in Nepal, with 1,000 of them in the capital,
The Kathmandu Post daily reported Monday, quoting a report by the
International Labor Organization.
</P>
<P>
The report noted that 20 percent of the girls are below the age
of 16, and most of them are forced into sex work at the early age
due to social and economic reasons including poverty and the
burden of heavy debts upon families.
</P>
<P>
It added that of the 200,000 Nepali women working in the
brothels of India, 22,000 range between 9-16 in age.
</P>
<P>
It was estimated that 5,000 to 7,000 Nepalese women and girls
are trafficked every year through the 1,750-kilometer-long open
border between Nepal and India. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
