<HEADLINE> Connors Edges McEnroe in Senior Tennis Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, September 27 (Xinhua) -- Jimmy Connors beat John
McEnroe 6-7, 6-2, 11-9 in the final of the senior tennis
tournament Sunday in Texas, the United States.
</P>
<P>
It was Connor's fourth tournament title of the year and
brought him 40,000 U.S. dollars. McEnroe won 25,000 dollars and
still has a 100-point lead on Connors in the Nuveen Masters point
standings.
</P>
<P>
It was the 41st meeting between the two American veterans.
McEnroe served 14 aces, but overall his serving percentage was a
low 50 percent.
</P>
<P>
In the match, McEnroe sparred with chair umpire, glared at the
linespeople and jawed back and forth with the crowd. Connors
glared at McEnroe, and walked off the court once. The two old
foes left the court without shaking hands. 
</P>
</TEXT>
