<DOCNO> XIE19980928.0201 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Nepali Government Offices Closed for Festival </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, September 28 (Xinhua) -- Government offices in Nepal
began Monday a week-long closure for the public servants to enjoy
Dashain, the biggest festival in the Himalayan kingdom.
</P>
<P>
All the educational institutions including schools and campuses
as well as courts are closed for 15 days, making Dashain one of
the longest festivals in the world.
</P>
<P>
The press takes a respite as well as all the publications in
the country will stop for at least four days.
</P>
<P>
To the Nepalese, the Hindus in particular, Dashain means
happiness, joy, fun and family reunion as well as victory by the
good over the evil.
</P>
<P>
In Nepal, all the people set up a sacred chamber at home, where
they worship Goddess Durga every morning and evening and grow
jamara, barley seeds planted in the sandy soil brought from the
holy river.
</P>
<P>
Durga temples in different places are thronged with devotees as
well at this time of the year.
</P>
<P>
People receive from the elders Tika, a red mark of combination
of rice, vermilion powder, curd and jamara as a symbol of
happiness, longevity, progress and prosperity.
</P>
<P>
The prime minister, ministers and other personalities gather at
the royal palace to receive Tika, jamara and blessings from the
king, just as the ordinary people do.
</P>
<P>
In Nepal, Dashain is also a moment for family reunion.
</P>
<P>
Wherever they may be, people try to join their families at this
time of the year.
</P>
<P>
On this occasion, the usually overcrowded and noisy Kathmandu
experiences a tranquillity hard to come by as more than half of
its population is said to desert it for hometowns.
</P>
<P>
New clothes, delicious food and merrymaking are desires of all
the families on the occasion.
</P>
<P>
For children living in the urban areas, playing colorful kites
under the sunny and blue sky is truly a great treat as the monsoon
season has gone. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
