<DOCNO> XIE19980928.0205 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bangladesh to Receive Aid From UNDP for Poverty Alleviation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, September 28 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations Development
Program (UNDP) will provide assistance totaling 7.73 million U.S.
dollars for two poverty alleviation projects in Bangladesh, said a
handout of the Press Information Department reaching here Monday.
</P>
<P>
The two agreements were signed between the two sides in Dhaka
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The UNDP will provide 5.36 million dollars to a rural
alleviation project in the northeast district of Kishoreganj and
2.37 million dollars to appropriate resources for improving
children's environment project.
</P>
<P>
These projects will provide a tangible contribution to national
efforts aimed at poverty alleviation and development of a national
strategy for empowerment of most vulnerable children.
</P>
<P>
Over half of Bangladesh's 127 million people are now living
under the poverty line. The government has been making relentless
efforts in poverty alleviation. 
</P>
