<HEADLINE> Drug Dealers Hit Hard in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, September 28 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai's anti-drug
campaign this summer has yielded remarkable achievements,
according to today's China Daily.
</P>
<P>
In August, the Shanghai police cracked one of the biggest drug
cases in the country with a 24-member drug ring smashed, the paper
said.
</P>
<P>
On August 31, 29.7 kilograms of heroin in the form of 58
cylinders and more than 80,000 yuan (9,660 US dollars) of drug
money were confiscated by the police when the head of the ring,
known as Ah Jiu, was caught in a hotel in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
Eight members of the ring were captured along with Ah
Jiu. Police had caught all the others since the investigation of
the case began in mid-July, the paper said.
</P>
<P>
In another development, nine people involved in four drug
trafficking cases were sentenced to death, life imprisonment and
term imprisonment, respectively, by the First Intermediate
People's Court of Shanghai on last Friday.
</P>
<P>
In the four cases, a total of 6,541 kilograms of heroin were
confiscated by the police. Ma Yongfu, 28, was given a death
penalty for transporting 800,000 yuan (96,600 US dollars) of drug
money from Shanghai to the northwestern province of Gansu,
according to the paper.
</P>
<P>
Various government departments, mainly police and customs, have
placed anti-smuggling high on their agendas in response to a
national meeting on smuggling held by the State Council in July.
</P>
<P>
In July and August, police across the country investigated
hundreds of smuggling cases involving hundreds of millions of
yuan, according to figures released at a national telephone
conference on combating smuggling held by the Ministry of Public
Security earlier this month.
</P>
<P>
Also in the aforementioned two months, frontier defence police
troops smashed a total of 77 drug trafficking cases, an official
with the Frontier Defence Bureau under the Ministry of Public
Security said.
</P>
<P>
Eightythree suspects were captured, and 219 kg of heroin, 66.65
kg of methamphetamine, and 10 tons of pharmaceutical preparations
for making drugs were confiscated, the official said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
