<HEADLINE> Hackett Breaks World 1500m Swimming Record </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, September 28 (Xinhua) -- Grant Hackett of Australia
broke the world men's 1500 meters freestyle shortcourse swimming
record at the Australian shortcourse national championships in
Perth on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Hackett, 18, clocked 14 minutes 19.55 seconds, trimming almost
seven seconds off compatriot Kieran Perkins' world record of 14
minutes 26.52 seconds, set in Auckland, New Zealand, five years
ago.
</P>
<P>
He was on world record time from the start of the race,
despite having no-one to push him. 
</P>
</TEXT>
