<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Olano Wins Tour of Spain Cycle Race </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, September 28 (Xinhua) -- Abraham Olano gave Spain
their first Tour of Spain cycle race triumph for seven years on
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The Basque rider completed the 3,781 kilometers and 22 days of
racing with 93 hours 44 mintues eight seconds, one minute 23
seconds ahead of compatriot Fernando Escartin.
</P>
<P>
Olano's team mate Jose Maria Jimenez was third, 2:12 in
Arrears, to give the hosts their first home bred one-two-three
since Melchor Mauri's victory in 1991 and only the second clean
sweep since 1976.
</P>
<P>
The final stage over 163-km was won by Switzerland's Marcus
Zberg with four hours 8 minutes 36 seconds in Cordoba.
</P>
<P>
Dutchman Max van Heeswijk was second and Italian Giancarlo
Raimondi third in the mass sprint finish on the Paseo de la
Castellana in the heart of the Spanish capital. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980928.0249 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> McGwire Closes Season with 70 Homers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, September 27 (Xinhua) -- Mark McGwire hit his 69th
and 70th homers on the season's last day, setting an incredible
record in the U.S. baseball history.
</P>
<P>
"This is a season I will never, ever forget, and I hope
nobody in baseball ever forgets it," McGwire told the cheering
crowd after the game in St. Louis.
</P>
<P>
The giant guy, who hit five homers on the final weekend, hit
his 69th in the third inning Sunday, then homered for the 70th in
the seventh.
</P>
<P>
Now, McGwire has dropped Sammy Sosa behind in the homer-fight
through the season, and his new record was nine better than the
37-year-old previous record set by Roger Maris.
</P>
<P>
Sosa stands with 66 homers so far. McGwire, has 10 multihomer
games this year and 53 in his career, hit a go-ahead homer for
the 24th time this season.
</P>
<P>
He opened the year with a slam on March 31, then led the home
run race all season except when Sosa twice passed him briefly.
</P>
<P>
Sosa led for 65th on August 19 before McGwire regained lead on
Friday when he hit his 66th on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Sunday was the Cardinals' final game of the season. Sosa's
Cubs, who played at Houston, did not know if their regular season
would end or if there would be a playoff game for the national
league wild-card spot.
</P>
<P>
McGwire has 180 homers the last three season. 
</P>
</TEXT>
