<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, September 27 (Xinhua) -- American Sharmba Mitchell
finally will get his chance to fight for a world title on October
10 when he faces World Boxing Association welterweight champion
Khalid Rahilou in Paris.
</P>
<P>
Mitchell, with a record of 42-2 including 29 knockouts, is the
WBA's No. 1 contender has not fought since a first-round TKO of
Bob Elkins on February 21.
</P>
<P>
The bout will be televised on Showtime in the United States.
The annual "Fight for Children" charity card is scheduled for
October 15 in Washington. In the main event, undefeated U.S.
Boxing Association interim junior welterweight champion Zabdiel
Judah will face Washington's Darryl Tyson. 
