<HEADLINE> U.S. Team Humilated in Davis Cup Tennis Semis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, September 27 (Xinhua) -- The starless U.S. team
lost to Italy 4-1 in the Davis Cup tennis semi-final on Sunday in
Milwaukee, the United States, ending its 18 winning streak on
home soil in the tournament.
</P>
<P>
Following a knockout 3-0 loss yesterday, Jan-Michael Gambill
survived a victory over Davide Sanguinetti 4-6, 6-3, 6-3 for the
host team in the second dead rubber match today.
</P>
<P>
American Justin Gimelstob lost to Italy's Gianluca Pozz on
Sunday in another singles.
</P>
<P>
Italy will face Sweden in the final on December 4.
</P>
<P>
Pete Sampras, Andre Agassi, Michael Chang and Jim Courier all
failed to join the U.S. team. So the U.S. squad had to choose two
21-year-old Davis Cup rookies and Todd Martin. Martin was dumped
in both singles and doubles.
</P>
<P>
"Even if we didn't bet the best USA team, for us it is still a
very good result," said dual winner Andrea Gaudenzi. 
</P>
</TEXT>
