<HEADLINE> Wimbledon Climb to Third </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 27 (Xinhua) -- Wimbledon moved up to third
place in the English premier league after playing with a 1-1 draw
against Leicester City on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Midfielder Robbie Earle rose well at a free kick to put the
London side ahead in the 75th minute and they looked to be
heading towards a victory.
</P>
<P>
But defender Matt Elliott headed home three minutes before the
end to give the home side a 1-1 draw.
</P>
<P>
Wimbledon, with 12 points from seven games, are level with
second-placed Derby County. Aston Villa have a five-point lead
at the top after their 1-0 defeat of Derby on Saturday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
