<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Clinton Greets Schroeder, Vows Close Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, September 27 (Xinhua) -- U.S. President Bill
Clinton Sunday called German chancellor-elect Gerhard Schroeder
to congratulate him on winning Germany's elections and pledged to
work closely with the new leader of Germany.
</P>
<P>
"Today the German people have once again exercised their
democratic rights to determine their national leadership," Clinton
said in a written statement.
</P>
<P>
"I extend my sincerest congratulations to Gerhard Schroeder,"
said Clinton who is raising fund for Democratic candidates in
Texas.
</P>
<P>
"I look forward to working closely with him. Germany is one of
America's closest allies. As always, our two governments will be
fully engaged in a comprehensive policy agenda," Clinton said.
</P>
<P>
As for Helmut Kohl, who was defeated by Schroeder, Clinton
offered warm words.
</P>
<P>
"I want to convey my gratitude and that of all Americans to
Helmut Kohl. During his 16-year tenure, he has made historic
contributions to the unity of his nation, the strength of our
Euro-Atlantic community and to peace throughout the world,"
Clinton said.
</P>
<P>
White House spokesman Barry Toiv said Clinton telephoned
Schroeder and spoke to him for about five minutes Sunday, but the
two men did not discuss plans to get together in person. Clinton
is also to call Kohl.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
